<%= back_to_lesson %>

<h3>Guidelines</h3>
<ul class = "unindented_ul">

	<li>Google your question first</li>
	<p>
		Becoming a great googler and getting your own answers is an essential skill to become a competent developer. Google is smarter than anyone, ask it first, and if you still don't understand, seek for assistance.</p>
	</p>

	<li>Ask good questions</li>
	<p>
		Bad questions will result in bad answers. Good questions are those which are specific, concise, and practical.
	</p>

	<li>See previous questions</li>
	<p>
		Has anyone else asked the same question? If so, read the answers to those questions first before seeking further assistance.
	</p>

</ul>

<br>

<%= simple_form_for :comment, url: forum_comments_path, method: :post, input_html: {class: 'form-horizontal'} do |f| %>
	<%= f.input :title, required: true %>
	<div data-no-turbolink>
		<%= f.cktext_area :description, as: :text, input_html: {rows: 6}, ckeditor: {language: 'us'}, required: true %>
	</div>
	<%= f.input :lesson, as: :hidden, input_html: { value: params[:lesson]} %>
	<%= f.input :forum_id, as: :hidden, input_html: { value: params[:forum_id]} %>

	<br>
	<%= f.submit 'Submit Question', class: 'btn btn-primary' %>
<% end %>